# Goals

---

## Auth-G1 User Login & RBAC Integration
**Status:** implemented
**Module:** auth
**Tags:** stack:both, module:auth
**Depends on:** Runtime-G3

- [x] Wire existing `backend/src/rbac/` module into main Axum app
- [x] Add JWT secret loading and persistence across restarts
- [x] Seed default admin user (admin/admin) on first run
- [x] Protect `/api/forge/*` routes with `auth_middleware`
- [x] Add public `/api/auth/login` and `/api/auth/register` endpoints
- [x] Implement Vue 3 `LoginView.vue` with login/register toggle
- [x] Implement `useAuth.ts` composable for JWT lifecycle and `authFetch()` wrapper
- [x] Add auth guard to `App.vue` showing LoginView when unauthenticated
- [x] Add user menu with logout in nav rail

AutoForge now requires authentication for all forge/relay/admin API calls. The RBAC backend provides SQLite-backed users, roles, and permissions; the frontend manages JWT tokens in `localStorage`.

## Auth-G2 Permission Enforcement on Forge/Relay Routes
**Status:** in_progress
**Module:** auth
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:auth
**Depends on:** Auth-G1

- [ ] Apply `require_permission()` middleware to forge/relay/config route groups
- [ ] Define minimum permission set (e.g., `forge:read`, `forge:write`, `relay:admin`)
- [ ] Validate permissions in integration tests
- [ ] Update frontend to handle 403 responses gracefully

Currently `auth_middleware` verifies authentication only; fine-grained permission enforcement is not yet active.

## Auth-G3 Role-Based UI
**Status:** proposed
**Module:** auth
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:auth
**Depends on:** Auth-G2

- [ ] Admin users see user/role management UI
- [ ] Hide restricted views based on `permissions` array
- [ ] Add "switch role" or "impersonate" helper for admins

Future enhancement once Auth-G2 permission enforcement is complete.
